      "params": "none",
      "example": "/bridge-kick"
    }

  },

  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  // MCP COMMAND FORM
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //
  // MCP-backed tools are surfaced as slash commands with the special marker:
  //
  //   /tool-name (MCP) [args]
  //
  // These are dynamically registered from enabled MCP servers and do NOT
  // appear in /help unless the relevant server is enabled.
  //
  // Example with the github MCP server enabled:
  //
  //   /create_pull_request (MCP) owner:anthropics repo:claude-code
  //   /search_repositories (MCP) q:claude-code language:typescript
  //
  // Use /mcp to see which servers are active and their available tools.
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  // ARGUMENT CONVENTIONS
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //
  //  <arg>        Required argument — command will fail / show help without it.
  //  [arg]        Optional argument — command works without it.
  //  a|b|c        Enumerated choices — exactly one of the listed values.
  //  [a|b]        Optional enumerated choice.
  //  [text]       Optional free-form string.
  //  <text>       Required free-form string.
  //
  // Arguments are a single trailing string — no flags parsing unless the
  // command explicitly splits on spaces or keywords internally.
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  // SPECIAL VARIABLES (inside skill / prompt commands)
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //
  //  $ARGUMENTS   — the full argument string passed after the command name
  //
  // Used in SKILL.md prompt templates, e.g.:
  //
  //   PROMPT: "Summarise the following: $ARGUMENTS"
  //
  // Then invoked as: /my-skill This is the text I want summarised
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

}
